@startuml
title Activity Diagram â€“ Part 1: Scene Setup & Asset Import

|Developer|
start
:Call loadScene(path);

|SceneLoader|
:Validate scene path;
if (Path is valid?) then (yes)
  :Parse scene metadata;
  :Create empty Three.js scene;
else (no)
  stop
endif

:Initialize ModelImporter;

|ModelImporter|
:Check model format (OBJ/GLTF);
:Load model file(s);
:Parse mesh data;
:Return Object3D instances;

|SceneLoader|
:Attach models to scene;

|MaterialHandler|
:Check for material files;
:Load textures;
:Assign materials to meshes;
if (Missing textures?) then (fallback)
  :Apply default material;
endif

|LightingManager|
:Initialize lighting config;
:Add directional and ambient lights;
:Set light intensity and position;

|EnvironmentHandler|
:Check HDRI file;
:Load environment texture;
:Apply to scene background and reflections;

|Developer|
stop
@enduml
